<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="22" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Burnley</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-12-15"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 15, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of Lord Lyons’s note of the 5th instant, together with its
                            accompanying copy of a despatch from the governor general of Canada,
                            relative to the schemes of the insurgents in Canada against the United
                            States.</p>
                        <p>Accept, sir, renewed assurance of my high consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>J <hi rend="smallcaps">Hume Burnley,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>